{
  "texts": [
    "XLM-T is different from Twitter-roBERTa mainly in its multilingual capacity because it was trained on tweets in eight languages, while Twitter-roBERTa was trained on English tweets only foot_1.",
    "All three models are publicly available as a Python package or on Hugging Face.",
    "For our analysis, we did not re-train or fine-tune the models.",
    "A more detailed description of the three models is included in Appendix A.1.",
    "We finalized the best model for our study by evaluating the performance of these models against the ground truth in a subset of our dataset."
  ]
}